dct_description_sm: Compass rose, rhumb lines, pictorial vignettes of figures, bird's eye view of village, ship, boats.
Index numbers appear on map but key not apparent.
Extensive descriptive text in gothic script below map.
Map appears on verso of Bry's Tabula terrae Nouae Zemblae in qua fretum sinusq Waigats item ord littorialis Tartariae atq Russiae, ad urgem usq Kildeinam / authore Gerhardo De Veer.
Depicts Barentsz' third voyage in search of a northeast passage.
Appears in Bry's Petit Voyages (Indiae Orientalis), Frankfurt am Main, 1613.
